   Yesterday I caught my first cobra of the new decade, and last night came my first mamba of the new decade! :D A Black Mamba had been seen slithering behind an oven, down in the Inanda Valley. "Never before in my life, have I seen a snake this big with my naked eyes", said the caller. He considered killing it but said it was too scary to do so, thankfully! The caller and his mate ran about 500m through the bush, up a steep slope, to meet us on the road, with no torch! It was a very bumpy drive to the house. The mamba was a feisty one, constantly moving behind one cupboard to another. We had some very intoxicated onlookers, who I was more worried about than the snake. After giving us the run around, we eventually got it! It's a beautiful specimen, a nice grey color and very healthy! Not a giant mamba, but a decent size nonetheless. #snakeconservation #snakes #snakesofinstagram #snakesofig #blackmamba #mambas #dendroaspispolylepis #venomous #venomoussnakes #durban #southafrica #africa #onlyinafrica #kzn #reptiles #reptilesofinstagram #conservation #inanda #summer #2020 #newyear #newdecade #wildlife #community

